{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_64","type":"reasoning","text":"**Considering button functionality**\n\nI think we have an issue with the Escape key not working properly during loading, likely due to focus problems. We could address this by ensuring the AppWindow key handler processes Escape first and resets loading status if necessary.  \n\nThere's also a potential problem with the A button; it might not be functioning because the unified controller sends `KEY_ENTER`, while the listeners only check for `Key.Return` and space. This discrepancy could definitely explain why the A button isn't working as intended.\n**Examining selection issues**\n\nIt looks like I’ve identified a strong root cause for the issues with P0 #2 and #3/#1. If the A button doesn't trigger, it makes selecting an item impossible. However, the user mentioned that selecting any media item leads to a loading black screen, so maybe the A button does work sometimes when used via click.  \n\nI should also consider if selecting items with the keyboard is possible. In the home.slint and content-row.slint files, they check for `Key.Return` or space. I need to inspect the key handler in login.slint as well."}}
