{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_66","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating loading issues**\n\nI’m thinking about the problem with the loading overlay where the focus scope does not allow exit, which might be causing a permanent black screen. It seems the network call could be hanging, preventing escape. I’ve considered adding a timeout since it’s already in a local diff but might not be committed yet. To address this, it makes sense to ensure all long loads have a timeout. I should verify if the local changes for the timeout are indeed uncommitted.\n**Investigating user loading crashes**\n\nI’m considering how to tackle the issue with the loading crash, particularly during user selection and login. It seems the loading hangs might be due to unbounded load operations. Adding timeouts around the login process and user selection could help, especially since API requests already time out at 15 seconds. However, processing images might take longer than expected, and I wonder if there are infinite loops in the items_to_media_items function. It’s worth inspecting quickly for any memory leaks or loop issues."}}
